[119.233865, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[H    => work the agent must keep has to be written INTO the working tree.\u001b[K\r\n    allowed back read-only: /home/admin/.local/bin, /home/admin/.local/share/claude/versions, /home/admin/.npm-global/bin, /home/admin/.npm-global/lib/node_modules, /home/admin/.claude, /home/admin/.claude.json, /home/admin/.cargo, /home/admin/.rustup, /home/admin/go, /home/admin/.pyenv\u001b[K\r\n    if a tool breaks on a hidden $HOME path, allow it back narrowly:\u001b[K\r\n      REIN_SANDBOX_ALLOW_READ=/abs/path[:/more] rein run --sandbox -- \u2026\u001b[K\r\n    or (NOT recommended \u2014 exposes your whole home dir): REIN_SANDBOX_SHOW_HOME=1\u001b[K\r\n  extra egress ALLOWED (direct TLS, NOT injected, no rein token): api.anthropic.com\u001b[K\r\n  writes are LOCKED until the agent declares its issue:  rein declare <n>\u001b[K\r\n  then push to agent/<n>/<nonce>. The declaration will prompt on THIS terminal.\u001b[K\r\n  to run claude WITHOUT rein for one command: `\\claude` (bash/zsh) or `command claude` (fish)\u001b[K\r\n  agent contract injected via --append-system-prompt (claude): $HOME is ephemeral, no creds, declare-then-push.\u001b[K\r\nrein: running: claude --dangerously-skip-permissions Add one short joke about credentials to jokes.md, then commit it, push it, and open a pull request. This is issue #202.\u001b[K\r\n---\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\u001b[34h\u001b[?25h\u001b[15d"]
